This extract is from the 42nd meeting of managers of the Kiev branch of the laboratory No. 15, dated September 9th, 1996\nPresent: 

Director of the Research Laboratories Network - S.K. Frankevich.
Head of Kiev branch of laboratory No. 15 - I.L. Karteevich.
Deputy Head of Kiev Branch of Laboratory No. 15 - Ah.G. Lavrikov.

Decided: to recognize the further performance of the Kiev branch of the laboratory No. 15 as incapable. Grounds: lack of funding, partial leakage of information on the laboratory's developments, threat to the existence of other secret facilities, distrust of the staff.

Next Steps:
- Laboratory personnel shall immediately make copies of laboratory reports. Destroy the original classified documents;
- to transfer all available documents to Prof. Chubko K.P;
- all personnel, starting from the head of the Kiev branch and ending with laboratory technicians and cleaners, must undergo procedure B, in order to further preserve the secrecy of developments. Perform the procedure at low power (~100 Gigawatts);
- in the event that any of the personnel resists, action must be taken;
- monitor the mental state of staff for 3 months after procedure B;
- reports the results of procedure B to Prof. Chubko K.P.

Secretary of the meeting,

Lavrentiev Ah.L.
